title: Kris Bryant cuts into Mets lead with RBI double
text:
Cubs rookie Kris Bryant got Chicago on the board with an RBI double to left field in the sixth inning of Game 2.
Dexter Fowler came around to score on the play.
Kris Bryant gives the #Cubs some life. #NLCS pic.twitter.com/nLBI4MMebB
— Matthew Schwerha (@MSchwerha) October 19, 2015
The Cubs had managed just a single hit prior to the inning. Mets starter Noah Syndergaard has 10 strikeouts in six innings of work.
The Mets jumped out to a 3-0 lead in the first inning following a home run from Daniel Murphy – his fifth of the postseason.
Mets take early lead over Cubs in Game 2 It was the first time in 25 starts that Cubs ace Jake Arrieta allowed a first-inning run.
